OL,3,CWimbledon prepares for hotter summers
OL,4,Cafter record-breaking heatwave
OL,6,FWimbledon's grounds team is planning
OL,7,Fhow to keep its courts in pristine
OL,8,Fcondition "five to 10 years in
OL,9,Fadvance" as record-breaking heatwaves
OL,10,Fare expected to become more frequent.
OL,12,FNeil Stubley, Wimbledon's head of
OL,13,Fcourts and horticulture, described
OL,14,Flooking after "the most scrutinised
OL,15,Fpiece of turf in the world" as a
OL,16,F"labour of love".
OL,26,@pD@KOUqD@HO]vD@OOUwD@[O]xD@AOUxD@PO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/9
