CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1782906492
OL,3,CWimbledon prepares for hotter summers
OL,4,Cafter record-breaking heatwave
OL,6,FWith Met Office scientists warning
OL,7,Ftemperatures in England could reach as
OL,8,Fhigh as 45C by 2056, Mr Stubley said
OL,9,Ffocus is now on making sure the right
OL,10,Fgrass is selected to survive the heat.
OL,12,FHe said: "We are finding that our
OL,13,Fsummers are becoming slightly warmer,
OL,14,Fwith spikes of good weather in small
OL,15,Fincrements, but also finding that the
OL,16,Fold days of long, drizzly, light rain
OL,17,Fare becoming less and less, but we're
OL,18,Fgetting more high-intense rainfall
OL,19,Fepisodes."
OL,26,@tD@JOU{D@JO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1782906492
OL,3,CWimbledon prepares for hotter summers
OL,4,Cafter record-breaking heatwave
OL,6,FHe added: "The grasses that we're
OL,7,Fselecting now ` they're more drought-
OL,8,Ftolerant and wear-tolerant ` help us
OL,9,Fon weeks like last week, where the
OL,10,Fgrass has a threshold where it starts
OL,11,Fto struggle."
OL,13,FCooler nights give the turf a chance
OL,14,Fto recover from scorching temperatures
OL,15,Fsuch as those experienced last week,
OL,16,Falong with extra water in targeted
OL,17,Fareas.
OL,26,@nD@KOUsD@MO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1782906492
OL,3,CWimbledon prepares for hotter summers
OL,4,Cafter record-breaking heatwave
OL,6,FBut he said if overnight temperatures
OL,7,Frise in future summers towards 29C or
OL,8,F30C, there will be little relief for
OL,9,Fplants.
OL,11,FRigorous testing of the grass carried
OL,12,Fout both before and during the grand
OL,13,Fslam help to keep the courts in top
OL,14,Fform, as well as tips Mr Stubley picks
OL,15,Fup from other sports grounds.
OL,17,FHe said: "I get to go to all the
OL,18,Fdifferent golf, football tournaments.
OL,26,@yD@JOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1782906492
OL,3,CWimbledon prepares for hotter summers
OL,4,Cafter record-breaking heatwave
OL,6,F"I can just pick up the phone to my
OL,7,Fcounterpart at Arsenal, and say, 'Can
OL,8,FI come and shadow you for a day?',
OL,9,Fjust to see how they manage their
OL,10,Fturf, because each sport will do it
OL,11,Fslightly different."
OL,13,FAside from the weather, the courts
OL,14,Fneed to adapt to other changes,
OL,15,Fincluding different styles of play and
OL,16,Fthe length of male and female players'
OL,17,Fmatches.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@TO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
